Package: autumn
Version: 0.2.0
Title: Fast, Modern, and Tidy-Friendly Iterative Raking
Description: Performs iterative proportional fitting (raking) to generate
    calibration weights for survey data. Implements DeBell and Krosnick (2009)
    iterative raking, Newton-Raphson calibration for severely imbalanced
    unbounded problems, SQUAREM-accelerated iterative proportional fitting,
    bounded water-filling redistribution (inline weight-cap enforcement without
    marginal displacement), automatic sparse-cell collapse with nearest-neighbour
    merging, outcome-aware design effect estimation via Henry and Valliant (2015),
    and a tidy-compatible interface. Forked from aaronrudkin/autumn.
